.TH KWIN-CTM-MONITOR 1 "July 2026" "kwin-ctm-monitor 0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kwin-ctm-monitor \- build and publish locally patched KDE neon KWin packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kwin-ctm-monitor
.BR status | check | build
.SH DESCRIPTION
The monitor detects a new KDE neon KWin source version, applies the packaged
CTM patch, validates it against VKMS in Docker, and publishes signed packages
to a machine-local APT repository. It never installs KWin packages.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Print the most recent monitor state.
.TP
.B check
Report the current Neon candidate and whether it has been published locally.
.TP
.B build
Build, validate, sign, and atomically publish the current candidate. Requires
root privileges.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/kwin-ctm-monitor.conf
Monitor configuration.
.TP
.I /var/lib/kwin-ctm-monitor
Status, signing key, retained builds, and signed APT repository.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/modules-load.d/kwin-ctm-monitor.conf
Persistent VKMS module configuration.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kwinctmctl (1),
.BR systemd.path (5)
